==English==

===Noun===

'''anomie'''

#Alienation or social instability caused by erosion of standards and values.

==Derivation==

From [[French]], via [[Greek]] ανομια (''anomiā'') 'lawlessness' from ανομος (''anomos'') 'lawless' from [[a-]] 'without' + νομος (''nomos'') 'law' from [[Indo-European]] root ''nem-''.

